      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">Lutetium is a silvery-white, hard and heavy metal. It belongs to the lanthanides and is the last of the series. On contact with air it oxidises superficially to form a layer of lutetium oxide – L</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">u</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="238">2</text>
      </subsup>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">O</text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="13" fc="0" fa="1" charset="238"></text>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">3</text>
      </subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">. Lutetium displaces hydrogen from water to form lutetium hydroxide  – Lu(OH</text>
      <subsup>
      <text fn="Arial" fh="15" fc="16777215" fa="1" charset="0">)</text>
